Conditional Statements:
 It provide different outcomes depending on the condition evaluated.
 Python uses indentation to identify a block.


■ 1) If Statement:
      Intepreter always check if statement.

⫸ Syntax:

if Condition:
  Statement
 or
  pass                        # In case if statement with no content, put in the pass statement to avoid getting an error.


# Code for If Statement
i)
a, b = 20, 10
if a > b:
  print("a is greater than b")

- O/P.:
a is greater than b



■ 2) If Else Statement:
      Intepreter check else statement only if "if" statement is false.

⫸ Syntax:

if (Condition):
  Statement
else:
  Statement


# Code for If Else Statement
i)
a, b = 10, 20
if (a > b):
  print("a is greater than b")
else:
  print("b is greater than a")

- O/P.:
b is greater than a



■ 3) Nested If Statement:

⫸ Syntax:

if (Condition):
  Statement
  if (Condition): 
    Statement
else:
  Statement


# Code for Nested If Statement
i)
a, b = 10, -20
if a > 0 & b > 0:
  if a > b:
    print("a is greater than b")
  else:
    print("b is greater than a")
else:
  print("Invalid Number")

- O/P.:
Invalid Number
